================================================================================
Bundled Dhivehi (Thaana) fonts
================================================================================

The application bundles a set of Thaana fonts under public/fonts/dhivehi/.
The vast majority were sourced via the raajjefonts.github.io catalogue, which
aggregates Dhivehi fonts that have circulated freely for many years from five
upstreams (dhivehi.mv archive, hassanhameed.com, thaana.com / Thaana Type
Foundry, thatmaldivesblog.wordpress.com, dhivehifont.com). A smaller set is
pre-bundled with rihaPDF from older Maldivian Windows installations and has
no formally documented author or license.

Known attributions:
  - Faruma — Mustafa Muhammad (calligraphy & design), Ibrahim Yasir
    (technical), Ahmed Aasif (refinement); 2002, commissioned by the
    Office of the President of the Maldives.
  - Faruma Arabic — sourced from https://github.com/muhammedjailam/FarumaArabic;
    upstream says it combines Faruma Font, Traditional Arabic, and AGA
    Arabesque Regular. Font metadata states: Version 1.0 Official release;
    Modified & Compiled by Mohamed Jailam; no separate license metadata
    is present.
  - ModFaruma — font metadata states: Version 2.0 Official release;
    created by Ibrahim Yasir, calligraphy by Musthafa Mohamed,
    assisted by Ahmed Asif; The President's Office 2002; all rights
    reserved; modified for rufiyaa symbol by Kudanai, 2023. No
    separate license metadata is present.
  - MV Boli — Thomas Rickner & Kamal Mansour (Monotype) for Microsoft;
    bundled with Microsoft Windows since XP.
  - MV Reethi — calligraphy by Abdul Sattar, Abdulla Waheed, Mustafa
    Muhammad; created by Ibrahim Yasir, assisted by Ahmed Aasif; 2002,
    commissioned by the Office of the President of the Maldives.
  - MV Waheed — calligraphy by Abdulla Waheed (1995); regular by
    Hassan Hameed; bold released 1996 with Accent Express.
  - Noto Sans Thaana — Google LLC, SIL Open Font License 1.1.

If you are a rights holder for any of these fonts and want it removed or
re-attributed, please open an issue at
https://github.com/yashau/rihaPDF/issues (or email ibrahim@yashau.com).

See public/fonts/dhivehi/README.md for the full inventory.

